19/* ************************************************************************************************************
20 JW October 10, 2015:
21 The PDK Framework handles all non-Finale-supported preference structures internally, instead of relying on the
22 code in finalepdk.cpp.
23
24 The PDK Framework tag versions are prefixed _fcpf_
25
26 The PDK Framework structures are prefixed _FCEDT
27
28 As of Finale 26.2, most preferences were rewritten to use new internal structures. But Finale still
29 contains a compatibility layer that emulates the old locations at kPreferencesCmper (65534). There appear
30 to be minor bugs in the emulation that impact a few scattered fields, but as of October 20, 2021, this
31 seems to be the cleanest approach for supporting old and new versions of Finale with a single binary.
32 To add direct support for the post-26.2 preference structs, make new FC classes that are only available
33 to Finale 26.2 or higher. This could be controlled at runtime in the Lua connector for JW Lua. --RGP
34***************************************************************************************************************/
35#define kPreferencesCmper ((CMPER)65534)
36
37#include "pragma_align_begin.h"
38struct _FCEDTPlaybackPrefs
39{
40 twobyte metronomeBeat; // EDU beat of the playback metronome (quarter note = 1024 EDUs etc).
41 // Setting this value will not automatically update the playback
42 // control visually.
43
44 twobyte metronomeSpeed; // Metronome speed number. Setting this value will not automatically
45 // update the playback control visually.
46
47 twobyte swing; // Swing value. swing = swing_value_for_display * 1024 / 100
48
49 twobyte baseKeyVelocity; // Base key velocity value
50
51 eMeas startAtMeas; // Always start at measure #, used when startAtMode is 0
52
53 twobyte startAtMode; // "Always start at:"
54 // 0 - Measure (startAtMeas is used)
55 // 1 - Leftmost measure
56 // 2 - Current Counter Setting
57
58 eMeas stopAtMeas; // Stop at measure #
59 // If stopAtMeas is EMEAS_MAX ==> End of Piece
60 // Otherwise, stopAtMeas should be 1 higher than the
61 // actual stop measure.
62 // For example: to stop at measure 5, stopAtMeas should be 6
63
64 FLAG_16 playbackRecordFlags; /* Flags from the Playback/Recording Options dialog box. */
65};
66#include "pragma_align_end.h"

124 Evpu16 timesigPartsBottomSymbolVert; // (parts) Time signatures - vertical adjustment of bottom
125 // time sig symbol from bottom staff line

536#include "pragma_align_begin.h"
537struct _FCEDTLyricsPrefs
538{
539 Evpu16 spaceBetweenHyphens; // Space between hyphens. In Fin2004, this is Maximum Space Between Hyphens Pos: ^15(65534) 1
540 Efix16 wordExtensionThickness; // Word Extension Line Thickness Pos: ^67(65534) 5
541
542 twobyte useSmartHyphens; // Pos: ^35(65534) 5
543 twobyte hyphenSystemStart; // Pos: ^57(65534) 0
544
545/* This data structure spans 2 incis at ^87(65534)
546 * */
547
548 twobyte othersSyllAlign; // Alignment options for other syllables Pos: ^87(65534) 1st inci 0
549 twobyte othersSyllJusti; // Justification options for other syllables Pos: ^87(65534) 1st inci 1
550 FLAG_16 flag; // Placeholder flag (no UI)
551
552 twobyte wordExtensionSyllAlign; // Alignment options Pos: ^87(65534) 1st inci 3
553 twobyte wordExtensionSyllJusti; // Justification options Pos: ^87(65534) 1st inci 4
554 FLAG_16 wordExtensionSyllFlags; // 0x8000 if Positioning of syllables with Word Extensions should be used Pos: ^87(65534) 1st inci 5
555
556 twobyte firstSyllAlign; // Alignment options Pos: ^87(65534), 2nd inci 0
557 twobyte firstSyllJusti; // Justification options Pos: ^87(65534), 2nd inci 1
558 FLAG_16 firstSyllFlags; // 0x8000 if Positioning of first syllables should be used Pos: ^87(65534), 2nd inci 2
559
560 twobyte startSysSyllAlign; // Alignment options Pos: ^87(65534) 2nd inci 3
561 twobyte startSysSyllJusti; // Justification options Pos: ^87(65534) 2nd inci 4
562 FLAG_16 startSysSyllFlags; // 0x8000 if Positioning of syllables on start of system should be used Pos: ^87(65534) 2nd inci 5
563};
564#include "pragma_align_end.h"

626enum PREFMAP_ARRAY_CONVERSION
627{
628 PFMC_NONE, /* No conversion */
629 PFMC_MACFOURBYTE, /* Fourbyte is stored in "Mac" manner (hiword+loword) */
630 PFMC_WINFOURBYTE, /* Fourbyte is stored in "Windows" manner (loword+hiword) */
631 PFMC_INVERTBOOL, /* The boolean state of a tbool should be inverted
632 before presenting it to the programmer */
633 PFMC_SIGNEDBYTE /* The twobyte might be stored as a signed byte; convert it to a
634 unsigned twobyte */
635};
636#endif /* #ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
637
642class __FCPrefsBase : public __FCBaseData
643{
644
645 /* Modified utility structures with their origin in finalepdk.cpp.
646 *
647 * Since there are bugs in the finalepdk.cpp implementation, and
648 * the structures causes too many workarounds the PDK Framework classes,
649 * it's better to not rely on finalepdk.cpp for the data that isn't
650 * directly supported by Finale.
651 */
652public:
653#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
654 struct PREFERENCE_LOCATION_MAPRECORD
655 {
656 bool bProcessed; /* For internal use */
657 char firstChar; /* First char of tag */
658 char secondChar; /* Second char of tag */
659 CMPER cmper; /* Cmper to load, if not 65534. For non-digit tags such as ^pd, 0 is used as an actual value. */
660 twobyte inci; /* Inci to load */
661 twobyte structOffset; /* offset within the struct */
662 twobyte offsetInInci; /* 0-based twobyte offset within the preference inci (0-5) */
663 twobyte bytesize; /* 2 - twobyte, 4 - fourbyte */
664 PREFMAP_ARRAY_CONVERSION conversion; /* Conversion */
665 EVERSION minversion; /* The minimum Finale version. Set to 0 to don't check. */
666 };
667#endif /* #ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
668private:
669
670#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
672 fourbyte MakePrefsFourbyte(const twobyte inci0, const twobyte inci1, const PREFMAP_ARRAY_CONVERSION convType);
673
675 void MakePrefsTwobytes(const fourbyte fb, twobyte *inci0, twobyte *inci1, const PREFMAP_ARRAY_CONVERSION convType);
676
678 bool MapPrefStruct(EXTAG tag,
679 twobyte prefNumber,
680 PREFERENCE_LOCATION_MAPRECORD **ppMapDef,
681 twobyte *noOfElements);
682#endif
683
684protected:
685
686#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
687
689 bool FragmentStructLoad(void* pVoidBuffer, fourbyte *pSize,
690 PREFERENCE_LOCATION_MAPRECORD *pMapDef, twobyte noOfElements);
691
693 bool FragmentStructSave(void* pVoidBuffer, fourbyte size,
694 PREFERENCE_LOCATION_MAPRECORD *pMapDef, twobyte noOfElements);
695
696#endif /* #ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
697
698public:
699 __FCPrefsBase() : __FCBaseData() { }
700
701 const char* ClassName() override { return "__FCPrefsBase"; }
702
705 bool Reload() override;
706
713 virtual bool Load(twobyte prefsno = 1);
714
715 bool Save() override;
716
717 bool LoadFirst() override { return Load(1); }
718
723 int GetItemNo() const { return _dataid.prefs.prefNumber; }
724};

2696 void SetPageMarginScope(
2697#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
2698 PAGEMARGINSCOPES
2699#else
2700 twobyte
2701#endif
2702 mode
2703 )
2704 {
2705 switch (mode)
2706 {
2707 case PAGEMARGINSCOPE_CURRENT:
2708 _prefsdata.layoutFlags &= ~LAYOUTFLG_ADJUST_PAGE_BITS;
2709 _prefsdata.layoutFlags |= LAYOUTFLG_ADJUST_PAGE_CUR;
2710 break;
2711 case PAGEMARGINSCOPE_ALL:
2712 _prefsdata.layoutFlags &= ~LAYOUTFLG_ADJUST_PAGE_BITS;
2713 _prefsdata.layoutFlags |= LAYOUTFLG_ADJUST_PAGE_ALL;
2714 break;
2715 case PAGEMARGINSCOPE_LEFTORRIGHT:
2716 _prefsdata.layoutFlags &= ~LAYOUTFLG_ADJUST_PAGE_BITS;
2717 _prefsdata.layoutFlags |= LAYOUTFLG_ADJUST_PAGE_LR;
2718 break;
2719 case PAGEMARGINSCOPE_RANGE:
2720 _prefsdata.layoutFlags &= ~LAYOUTFLG_ADJUST_PAGE_BITS;
2721 _prefsdata.layoutFlags |= LAYOUTFLG_ADJUST_PAGE_RNG;
2722 break;
2723 }
2724 }

3255#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
3256 void DebugDump() override
3257 {
3258 __FCPrefsBase::DebugDump();
3259 switch (GetPlacementMode())
3260 {
3261 case FCTuplet::TUPLETPLACEMENT_MANUAL:
3262 DebugOut("Placement mode: Manual");
3263 break;
3264 case FCTuplet::TUPLETPLACEMENT_STEMSIDE:
3265 DebugOut("Placement mode: Stem/Beam Side");
3266 break;
3267 case FCTuplet::TUPLETPLACEMENT_NOTESIDE:
3268 DebugOut("Placement mode: Note Side");
3269 break;
3270 case FCTuplet::TUPLETPLACEMENT_ABOVE:
3271 DebugOut("Placement mode: Above");
3272 break;
3273 case FCTuplet::TUPLETPLACEMENT_BELOW:
3274 DebugOut("Placement mode: Below");
3275 break;
3276 }
3277 DebugOutBool("Engraver tuplet: ", GetEngraverTuplet());
3278 DebugOutBool("Avoid staff: ", GetAvoidStaff());
3279 DebugOutBool("Allow horizontal drag: ", GetAllowHorizontalDrag());
3280 DebugOutBool("Use bottom note: ", GetUseBottomNote());
3281 switch (GetNumberStyle())
3282 {
3283 case FCTuplet::TUPLETNUMBER_NONE:
3284 DebugOut("Number appearance: None");
3285 break;
3286 case FCTuplet::TUPLETNUMBER_REGULAR:
3287 DebugOut("Number appearance: Number");
3288 break;
3289 case FCTuplet::TUPLETNUMBER_RATIO:
3290 DebugOut("Number appearance: Ratio");
3291 break;
3292 case FCTuplet::TUPLETNUMBER_RATIOANDNOTE:
3293 DebugOut("Number appearance: 7:8q");
3294 break;
3295 case FCTuplet::TUPLETNUMBER_RATIOANDNOTE_BOTH:
3296 DebugOut("Number appearance: 7q:8q");
3297 break;
3298 }
3299 switch (GetShapeStyle())
3300 {
3301 case FCTuplet::TUPLETSHAPE_NONE:
3302 DebugOut("Shape appearance: None");
3303 break;
3304 case FCTuplet::TUPLETSHAPE_BRACKET:
3305 DebugOut("Shape appearance: Bracket");
3306 break;
3307 case FCTuplet::TUPLETSHAPE_SLUR:
3308 DebugOut("Shape appearance: Slur");
3309 break;
3310 }
3311
3312 DebugOutBool("Break slur of bracket: ", GetBreakSlurBracket());
3313 switch (GetBracketMode())
3314 {
3315 case FCTuplet::TUPLETBRACKET_ALWAYS:
3316 DebugOut("Always use specified shape");
3317 break;
3318 case FCTuplet::TUPLETBRACKET_UNBEAMEDONLY:
3319 DebugOut("Bracket unbeamed notes only");
3320 break;
3321 case FCTuplet::TUPLETBRACKET_NEVERBEAMEDONBEAMSIDE:
3322 DebugOut("Never bracket beamed notes on beam side");
3323 break;
3324 }
3325 DebugOutInt("Horizontal offset: ", GetHorizontalOffset());
3326 DebugOutInt("Vertical offset: ", GetVerticalOffset());
3327 DebugOutBool("Center number using duration: ", GetCenterUsingDuration());
3328 DebugOutBool("Ignore Horizontal Number Offset: ", GetIgnoreNumberOffset());
3329 DebugOutInt("Horizontal shape offset: ", GetHorizontalShapeOffset());
3330 DebugOutInt("Vertical shape offset: ", GetVerticalShapeOffset());
3331 DebugOutBool("Always flat: ", GetAlwaysFlat());
3332 DebugOutBool("Bracket full duration: ", GetBracketFullDuration());
3333 DebugOutBool("Match length of hooks: ", GetMatchHookLengths());
3334 DebugOutInt("Left hook length: ", GetLeftHookLength());
3335 DebugOutInt("Left hook extension: ", GetLeftExtension());
3336 DebugOutInt("Right hook length: ", GetRightHookLength());
3337 DebugOutInt("Right hook extension: ", GetRightExtension());
3338 DebugOutInt("Manual slope adjustment: ", GetSlopeAdjust());
3339 }

4361 void SetScalingValue(int value)
4362 {

4365 _prefsdata.scalingFactorHigh = (fbRatio & 0xffff0000) >> 16;

4367
4378 void SetScalingFactor(double ratio)
4379 {
4380 ratio *= 10000;
4381 ufourbyte fbRatio = (ufourbyte) ratio;
4382 _prefsdata.scalingFactorLow = fbRatio & 0xffff;
4383 _prefsdata.scalingFactorHigh = (fbRatio & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
4384 }

4471 void SetGraceNoteSpacingMode(
4472#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
4473 GRACENOTE_SPACINGMODE

4477 value

4485
4492 void SetManualPositioning(
4493#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
4494 MANUAL_POSITIONING
4495#else
4496 int
4497#endif
4498 value
4499 )
4500 {
4501 switch (value)
4502 {
4503 case MANUALPOS_CLEAR:
4504 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_CLRPOSITS, true);
4505 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_USEPOSITS, false);
4506 break;
4507 case MANUALPOS_INCORPORATE:
4508 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_CLRPOSITS, false);
4509 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_USEPOSITS, true);
4510 break;
4511 case MANUALPOS_IGNORE:
4512 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_CLRPOSITS, false);
4513 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_USEPOSITS, false);
4514 break;
4515 }
4516 }
4517
4524 void SetUnisonsMode(
4525#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
4526 UNISONS_MODE
4527#else
4528 int
4529#endif
4530 value
4531 )
4532 {
4533 switch (value)
4534 {
4535 case UNISSPACE_ALLNOTEHEADS:
4536 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_AVCOLUNISONS_ALL, true);
4537 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_AVCOLUNISONS_SAME, false);
4538 break;
4539 case UNISSPACE_DIFFERENTNOTEHEADS:
4540 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_AVCOLUNISONS_ALL, false);
4541 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_AVCOLUNISONS_SAME, true);
4542 break;
4543 case UNISSPACE_NONE:
4544 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_AVCOLUNISONS_ALL, false);
4545 Set16BitFlag(&_prefsdata.flag, MSP_AVCOLUNISONS_SAME, false);
4546 break;
4547 }
4548 }
4549

4811 bool GetFontInfo(FCFontInfo* pFontInfo)
4812 {
4813 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return false;
4814 pFontInfo->SetEnigmaStyles(_prefsdata.efx);
4815 pFontInfo->SetSize(_prefsdata.size);
4816 pFontInfo->SetNameByID(_prefsdata.font);
4817 return true;
4818 }
4819
4829 FCFontInfo* CreateFontInfo()
4830 {
4831 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return NULL;
4832 FCFontInfo* pFontInfo = new FCFontInfo();
4833 pFontInfo->SetEnigmaStyles(_prefsdata.efx);
4834 pFontInfo->SetSize(_prefsdata.size);
4835 pFontInfo->SetNameByID(_prefsdata.font);
4836 return pFontInfo;
4837 }
4838
4839#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY_CPP
4841 luabridge::RefCountedPtr<FCFontInfo> CreateFontInfo_GC()
4842 { return CreateFontInfo(); }
4843#endif
4844
4854 bool SetFontInfo(FCFontInfo* pFontInfo)
4855 {
4856 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return false;
4857 _prefsdata.efx = pFontInfo->GetEnigmaStyles();
4858 _prefsdata.size = pFontInfo->GetSize();
4859 _prefsdata.font = pFontInfo->GetNameByID();
4860 return true;
4861 }

5835
5840 void CloneMemoryFrom(__FCBaseData* pSource) override
5841 {
5842 memcpy(&_prefsdata, ((FCSlurContourPrefs*)pSource)->_GetPrefsData(), sizeof(_prefsdata));
5843 _datablock = &_prefsdata;
5844 _loadedsize = sizeof(_prefsdata);
5845 }
5846
5847 __FCBaseData* CreateObject() override { return new FCSlurContourPrefs(); }
5848public:
5849#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
5851 void* _GetPrefsData() { return &_prefsdata; }
5852#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
5853
5854 const char* ClassName() override { return "FCSlurContourPrefs"; }
5855 const PDKFRAMEWORK_CLASSID GetClassID() const override { return FCID_SLURCONTOURPREFS; }
5856
5857 FCSlurContourPrefs() :
5858 __FCPrefsBase()
5859 {
5860 memset(&_prefsdata, 0, sizeof(_prefsdata));
5861 }
5862
5869 twobyte CalcInset(int slurlength)
5870 {
5871 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return 0;
5872 if (slurlength <= _prefsdata.shortSpan.def) return _prefsdata.shortSpan.inset;
5873 ESlurContourDefaults* pShorterDefaults = NULL;
5874 ESlurContourDefaults* pLongerDefaults = NULL;
5875 if (slurlength <= _prefsdata.mediumSpan.def)
5876 {
5877 pShorterDefaults = &_prefsdata.shortSpan;
5878 pLongerDefaults = &_prefsdata.mediumSpan;
5879 }
5880 else if (slurlength <= _prefsdata.longSpan.def)
5881 {
5882 pShorterDefaults = &_prefsdata.mediumSpan;
5883 pLongerDefaults = &_prefsdata.longSpan;
5884 }
5885 else
5886 {
5887 pShorterDefaults = &_prefsdata.longSpan;
5888 pLongerDefaults = &_prefsdata.extraLongSpan;
5889 }
5890
5891 /* If the width isn't extremely short or long span, calculate */
5892 int evpuoffset = slurlength - pShorterDefaults->def;
5893 int heigthspandiff = pLongerDefaults->inset - pShorterDefaults->inset;
5894 int evpuspan = pLongerDefaults->def - pShorterDefaults->def;
5895 return pShorterDefaults->inset + evpuoffset * heigthspandiff / evpuspan;
5896 }
5897
5904 twobyte CalcHeight(int slurlength)
5905 {
5906 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return 0;
5907 if (slurlength <= _prefsdata.shortSpan.def) return _prefsdata.shortSpan.height;
5908 ESlurContourDefaults* pShorterDefaults = NULL;
5909 ESlurContourDefaults* pLongerDefaults = NULL;
5910 if (slurlength <= _prefsdata.mediumSpan.def)
5911 {
5912 pShorterDefaults = &_prefsdata.shortSpan;
5913 pLongerDefaults = &_prefsdata.mediumSpan;
5914 }
5915 else if (slurlength <= _prefsdata.longSpan.def)
5916 {
5917 pShorterDefaults = &_prefsdata.mediumSpan;
5918 pLongerDefaults = &_prefsdata.longSpan;
5919 }
5920 else
5921 {
5922 pShorterDefaults = &_prefsdata.longSpan;
5923 pLongerDefaults = &_prefsdata.extraLongSpan;
5924 }
5925
5926
5927 /* If the width isn't extremely short or long span, calculate */
5928 int evpuoffset = slurlength - pShorterDefaults->def;
5929 int heigthspandiff = pLongerDefaults->height - pShorterDefaults->height;
5930 int evpuspan = pLongerDefaults->def - pShorterDefaults->def;
5931 return pShorterDefaults->height + evpuoffset * heigthspandiff / evpuspan;
5932 }
5933
5935 twobyte GetShortSpan()
5936 {
5937 return _prefsdata.shortSpan.def;
5938 }
5939
5941 twobyte GetMediumSpan()
5942 {
5943 return _prefsdata.mediumSpan.def;
5944 }
5945
5947 twobyte GetLongSpan()
5948 {
5949 return _prefsdata.longSpan.def;
5950 }
5951
5953 twobyte GetExtraLongSpan()
5954 {
5955 return _prefsdata.extraLongSpan.def;
5956 }
5957
5958#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
5959 void DebugDump() override
5960 {
5961 __FCPrefsBase::DebugDump();
5962 }
5963#endif
5964};

7779#define FCMUSICCHARPREFS_TWOBYTEPTR(structmember) \
7780 ((twobyte*)(_Use2012Version() \
7781 ? _GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs2012, structmember)) \
7782 : _GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs, structmember))))
7783
7784#define FCMUSICCHARPREFS_VOIDPTR(structmember) \
7785 ((void*)(_Use2012Version() \
7786 ? _GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs2012, structmember)) \
7787 : _GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs, structmember))))
7788
7789#define FCMUSICCHARPREFS_RETURNSYMBOLCHAR(structmember) \
7790 if (_Use2012Version()) \
7791 return *((eUniChar32*) _GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs2012, structmember))); \
7792 else \
7793 return *((twobyte*) _GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs, structmember)));
7794
7795#define FCMUSICCHARPREFS_SETSYMBOLCHAR(structmember, charslot) \
7796 if (_Use2012Version()) \
7797 *((eUniChar32*) _GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs2012, structmember))) = charslot; \
7798 else \
7799 *((twobyte*) _GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs, structmember))) = (charslot & 0xff);
7800
7801
7802#else
7803
7804/* Macros for pre-Finale 2012 PDKs */

7807
7808#define FCMUSICCHARPREFS_VOIDPTR(structmember) \
7809 ((void*)(_GetElementPtr(offsetof(EDTMusicCharsPrefs, structmember))))
7810

7813

9386 {

9388 _datablock = &_prefsdata;
9389 _loadedsize = sizeof(_prefsdata);
9390 }

9393 { return new FCPartScopePrefs(); }

9398#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
9399

9401 const PDKFRAMEWORK_CLASSID GetClassID() const override { return FCID_PARTSCOPEPREFS; }

10142
10151 int GetCount() const
10152 {
10153 for (int i = 1; i <= GetMaxElementCount(); i++)
10154 {
10155 if (GetNoteheadCharacter(i) == 0) return i - 1;
10156 }
10157 return GetMaxElementCount();
10158 }
10159
10170 int FindIndex(FCString* pFontName, eUniChar32 character)
10171 {
10172 if (!pFontName) return -1;
10173 FCFontInfo namefontinfo;
10174 namefontinfo.SetNameString(pFontName);
10175 twobyte namefontID = namefontinfo.GetNameByID();
10176 for (int i = 1; i <= GetMaxElementCount(); i++)
10177 {
10178 if (GetNoteheadCharacter(i) != character) continue;
10179 if (namefontID == GetFontID(i)) return i;
10180 }
10181 return -1;
10182 }
10183
10195 int ElementsExpand(int noofnewelements);
10196
10197#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
10198 void DebugDump() override
10199 {
10200 __FCPrefsBase::DebugDump();
10201 for (int i = 0; i < GetMaxElementCount(); i++)
10202 {
10203 DebugOutInt("Index: ", i);
10204 DebugOutInt("Character: ", GetNoteheadCharacter(i));
10205 FCFontInfo fontinfo;
10206 fontinfo.SetNameByID(GetFontID(i));
10207 DebugOutString("Font name: ", fontinfo.GetName());
10208 }
10209 }
10210#endif
10211};

11684
11689 bool GetNameHeaderFontInfo(FCFontInfo* pFontInfo)
11690 {
11691 if (!pFontInfo) return false;
11692 /* Name */
11693 if (_prefsdata.partNameHeaderUseFontID != 0)
11694 {
11695 /* Use font */
11696 pFontInfo->SetNameByID(_prefsdata.partNameHeaderFontID);
11697 }
11698 else
11699 {
11700 /* Default font */
11701 FCFontPrefs deffontprefs;
11702 deffontprefs.Load(FCFontPrefs::FONTPREF_TEXTBLOCK);
11703 FCFontInfo deffontinfo;
11704 deffontprefs.GetFontInfo(&deffontinfo);
11705 pFontInfo->SetNameByID(deffontinfo.GetNameByID());
11706 }
11707
11708 /* Size */
11709 if (_prefsdata.partNameHeaderFontSize == 0)
11710 {
11711 /* Default size */
11712 FCFontPrefs deffontprefs;
11713 deffontprefs.Load(FCFontPrefs::FONTPREF_TEXTBLOCK);
11714 FCFontInfo deffontinfo;
11715 deffontprefs.GetFontInfo(&deffontinfo);
11716 pFontInfo->SetSize(deffontinfo.GetSize());
11717 }
11718 else
11719 pFontInfo->SetSize(_prefsdata.partNameHeaderFontSize);
11720 /* Style*/
11721 pFontInfo->SetEnigmaStyles(_prefsdata.partNameHeaderFontEfx);
11722 return true;
11723 }
11724
11729 bool GetOpenExtractedParts() const { return _prefsdata.openExtractedParts != 0; }
11730
11735 bool GetSpaceSystemsEvenly() const { return _prefsdata.spaceSystemsEvenly != 0; }
11736
